50|$|<b>Cathodoluminescence</b> is {{the most}} {{important}} tool paleontologists have for revealing whether or not the calcium in fossil eggshell has been altered. Calcite in eggshell is either pure or rich in calcium carbonate. However, the calcite composing the egg can be altered after burial to include significant calcium content. <b>Cathodoluminescence</b> causes calcite altered in this fashion to glow orange.|$|E
