50|$|Recently, <b>cathodoluminescence</b> {{performed}} in electron microscopes {{is also being}} used to study surface plasmon resonances in metallic nanoparticles. Surface plasmons in metal nanoparticles can absorb and emit light, though the process {{is different from that}} in semiconductors. Similarly, <b>cathodoluminescence</b> has been exploited as a probe to map the local density of states of planar dielectric photonic crystals and nanostructured photonic materials.|$|E
